<p>If Kant counters are flawless anomaly detectors, then the Foundation's job is rendered basically trivial (especially since it follows that SRAs are universal neutralizers, since Kant counters are SRAs).</p>
<p>Realistically most anomolies investigated by the Foundation should turn out to be explicable, just due to probability. The only reason that -EX articles don't outnumber the mainlist in real life is that nobody actually wants to read thousands of fictional examples of expiremental error, unrepeatable results and hoaxes but we probably should still imagine that these articles exist in-universe. The Foundation, not being idiots, knows this, and they would have known it in 1920 too.</p>

